The official dates SARS has given for filing taxes are July 1 to October 24, 2022, and registered provisional and individual taxpayers who file via the e-filing portal have July 1, 2022, to January 23, 2023.  1. Contribute towards a retirement fund
2. Open up a tax-free savings account
3. Donate to a SARS-registered charity   4. Join a medical aid scheme
5. Keep a logbook if you receive a travel allowance
6. Keep a logbook if you drive a company car
7. Claim commission-related expenses if you are a commission earner  8. Claim business travel if you are a commission earner
